<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="69351" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="69351">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="69351">
Austria, Czechia, Estonia, Germany, Finland, France, Hungary, Latvia, Lithuania, North Macedonia, Moldova, Slovakia, Sweden, Ukraine (
<bibRefCitation author="Korneyev, V. A." journalOrPublisher="Entomological Review (Washington" pageId="0" pageNumber="69351" pagination="117 - 132" refId="B7077985" refString="Korneyev, V. A., White, I. M., 1991. Fruit flies of the genus Urophora R.-D. (Diptera, Tephritidae) of the East Palearctic. I. A key to subgenera and review of species (except the subgenus Urophora Urophora s. str. Entomological Review (Washington 70 (8): 117 - 132" title="Fruit flies of the genus Urophora R. - D. (Diptera, Tephritidae) of the East Palearctic. I. A key to subgenera and review of species (except the subgenus Urophora Urophora s. str" volume="70" year="1991">Korneyev and White 1991</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Merz, B." journalOrPublisher="Linzer Biologische Beitrge" pageId="0" pageNumber="69351" refId="B7078136" refString="Merz B Korneyev VA Fauna Europaea: Tephritidae. Fauna Europaea version 2.4 https://fauna-eu.org" year="2008">Merz and Korneyev 2011</bibRefCitation>
); Russia, east to southern Siberia (Krasnoyarsk); Kazakhstan; Turkmenistan; Uzbekistan; Kyrghyzstan (
<bibRefCitation author="Korneyev, V. A." journalOrPublisher="Entomological Review (Washington" pageId="0" pageNumber="69351" pagination="117 - 132" refId="B7077985" refString="Korneyev, V. A., White, I. M., 1991. Fruit flies of the genus Urophora R.-D. (Diptera, Tephritidae) of the East Palearctic. I. A key to subgenera and review of species (except the subgenus Urophora Urophora s. str. Entomological Review (Washington 70 (8): 117 - 132" title="Fruit flies of the genus Urophora R. - D. (Diptera, Tephritidae) of the East Palearctic. I. A key to subgenera and review of species (except the subgenus Urophora Urophora s. str" volume="70" year="1991">Korneyev and White 1991</bibRefCitation>
); Iran (
<bibRefCitation author="Zarghani, E." journalOrPublisher="Vestnik Zoologii" pageId="0" pageNumber="69351" pagination="123 - 134" refId="B7078279" refString="Zarghani, E., Khaghaninia, S., Mohamadzade Namin, S., Karimpour, Y., Korneyev, V. A., 2016. First records of the fruit flies (Diptera, Tephritidae) in the fauna of Iran. Vestnik Zoologii 50 (2): 123 - 134" title="First records of the fruit flies (Diptera, Tephritidae) in the fauna of Iran" volume="50" year="2016">Zarghani et al. 2016</bibRefCitation>
). The species (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStartId="F7139398" pageId="0" pageNumber="69351">1</figureCitation>
<figureCitation captionStartId="F7139403" pageId="0" pageNumber="69351">a</figureCitation>
) is here recorded as 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69351">new to Italy</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="69351" type="biology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="69351">Biology</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="69351">
The biology of 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. stigma" pageId="0" pageNumber="69351" rank="species" species="stigma">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69351">E. stigma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is poorly known. The flies are said to have been reared from 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Leucanthemum" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Leucanthemum vulgare" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="69351" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulgare">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69351">Leucanthemum vulgare</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Lam. (
<bibRefCitation author="Roser, K. L. F." journalOrPublisher="Correspondenzblatt des Koeniglich Wuerttembergischen Landwirthschaftlichen Vereins, Stuttgart" pageId="0" pageNumber="69351" pagination="49 - 64" refId="B7078235" refString="Roser, K. L.F., 1840. Erster Nachtrag zu dem im Jahre 1834 bekannt gemachten Verzeichnisse in Wurttemberg vorkommender zweiflugliger Insekten. Correspondenzblatt des Koeniglich Wuerttembergischen Landwirthschaftlichen Vereins, Stuttgart 37 (1): 49 - 64" title="Erster Nachtrag zu dem im Jahre 1834 bekannt gemachten Verzeichnisse in Wurttemberg vorkommender zweiflugliger Insekten" volume="37" year="1840">Roser 1840</bibRefCitation>
, as &quot; 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C.Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Chrysanthemum" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Chrysanthemum leucanthemum" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="69351" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="leucanthemum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69351">Chrysanthemum leucanthemum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot;), 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Achillea" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Achillea millefolium" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="69351" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="millefolium">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69351">Achillea millefolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. (
<bibRefCitation author="Loew, H." journalOrPublisher="Wien" pageId="0" pageNumber="69351" refId="B7078057" refString="Loew, H., 1862. Die europaeische Bohrfliegen (Trypetidae). Wien" title="Die europaeische Bohrfliegen (Trypetidae)" year="1862">Loew 1862</bibRefCitation>
: 68), 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Anthemis" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Anthemis arvensis" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="69351" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="arvensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69351">Anthemis arvensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. (
<bibRefCitation author="Korneyev, V. A." journalOrPublisher="Science Publishers, Enfield, New Hampshire, USA" pageId="0" pageNumber="69351" refId="B7078011" refString="Korneyev, V. A., Zwoelfer, H., Seitz, A., 2005. Biology, ecology and evolution of gall-inducing arthropods. Science Publishers, Enfield, New Hampshire, USA" title="Biology, ecology and evolution of gall-inducing arthropods" year="2005">Korneyev et al. 2005</bibRefCitation>
; forming small non-lignified galls in a single flower head), 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. cotula" pageId="0" pageNumber="69351" rank="species" species="cotula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69351">A. cotula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. (
<bibRefCitation author="Hendel, F." journalOrPublisher="Die Fliegen der palaearktischen Region" pageId="0" pageNumber="69351" refId="B7081928" refString="Hendel, F., 1927. . Die Fliegen der palaearktischen Region 5" volume="5" year="1927">Hendel 1927</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Tanacetum" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Tanacetum vulgare" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="69351" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulgare">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69351">Tanacetum vulgare</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. (
<bibRefCitation author="Merz, B." journalOrPublisher="Diptera: Tephritidae. Insecta Helvetica Fauna" pageId="0" pageNumber="69351" refId="B7078096" refString="Merz, B., 1994. . Diptera: Tephritidae. Insecta Helvetica Fauna 10" volume="10" year="1994">Merz 1994</bibRefCitation>
), but there are no comprehensive rearing data or descriptions of its biology.
</paragraph>
